  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0db3\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db3\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dad\u0dcf 5000\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d94\u0d9a\u0db3 \u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0d9a\u0dad\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0db8\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "5000 to Kataragama via Okanda seeking help from Kandasurindu",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Dishan Wickramaratne Gunasekera, buried in Basnayake Nilame of Ruhunu Kataragama Maha Devalaya, and Diyawadana Nilame Nilanga Dela of Monaragala Disapati Gunadasa Samarasinghe Dalada Maliga came near Okanda Devalaya to welcome the pilgrims who come from the north east on foot for the annual festival of Ruhunu Maha Kataragama Temple.",
        "Nearly 5000 devotees from the North East are coming to the historic Kataragama shrine through the Yala Forest Park.",
        "Devotees who enter the Yala Park near the Okada Temple spend many days seeking the help of the historical Kandasurindun.",
        "The police, wildlife officers and government officials have made arrangements to provide basic facilities such as water and food to these pilgrims."
      ],
